<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_a984d9e8-7d25-4c9d-995f-08a95a7749bd" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>5.7.2</sptc><title id="_fc596932-59ad-4fb2-abcc-55ec9de6c439">Cavities</title><archive-num>2019: 3.3.5.6</archive-num><subclause id="_f87240ec-9a53-419e-a28a-1481d7c99456" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_1a7e0941-016c-42e6-bc2f-e841b92b399d">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>For masonry veneer, the clear width of a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_5d845e20-ab31-4d80-bac6-a52b59eb71e9" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> between the masonry veneer and the exterior face of the supporting frame must not be—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_633777c6-37e7-4c42-8263-967c57f98b62">less than 25 mm wide; and</li><li id="_70465f1f-d5fc-43bd-8f7d-1cb561e68b57">more than 75 mm wide.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_b61a29df-023e-4041-9a68-dd33b1686789" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c67f72a2-583d-4ea4-9930-667a9e389a4a">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>For <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_b7e3cb4b-50ab-4ede-84d0-d70fa88d8db3" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> masonry, the clear width of a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_82380190-c2ef-41ee-9200-f121e20e2c50" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> between the inner and outer masonry leaves must not be—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_cb6a1885-988f-41a9-9bca-f9355fca2c5c">less than 35 mm; and</li><li id="_ace6296b-72fc-4ede-be6f-4da13d5d371f">more than 75 mm.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_5152c75b-5f39-48c8-8b54-cd88b7e68aca" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_00ae898e-61fa-45db-a2b3-ab5364e7936a">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Where masonry veneer and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_ded4573f-4270-4c8d-9f44-5e6d0585a092" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> masonry in (1) and (2) are constructed on a slab-on-ground, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_58be3154-25df-4a9f-9cad-76d06e8e94b9" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> must be drained to the outside in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1162_1.10.0.xml#_4fce11eb-3d03-4707-a797-697139fd3f64" id="_eb7ac50a-f762-4981-8f03-78b3a1666df6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">5.7.5</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_9ba3648d-048b-4833-9f92-3fbd1b279b72" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b3325f46-96e7-4102-b7ee-1be3f9aa2396">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>The exterior masonry leaf must not overhang the edge of the slab by more than 15 mm.</p></subclause><callout id="_4f59cc94-9f3a-4a66-b43f-ffe66d4c6940"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>The 25 mm clear width of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_675fcb72-a4e8-4ec3-b8ae-e841940dfad5" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> needs to be maintained regardless of any wall <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_3d3da4f0-855a-422c-8da5-76bce3c7dc53" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membranes</xref>, sheet bracing or services installed to the supporting frame.</p><p>Where mullions are located within a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1214_0.9.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_8e9e5a6f-426a-4093-917f-f8a1227fed89" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref>, a vertical <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1235_0.7.0.xml#_0d21b1c5-7e4f-446c-99a0-4c7564ed7952" id="_5b2a7b4f-4240-4e00-b4ca-f33f14e16d76" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">damp-proof course</xref> must be placed between the outer masonry leaf and the mullion to prevent moisture penetration.</p></callout></clause>